ies. Based on Oyman Başaran’s extensive ethnographic and historical research, Circumcision and Medicine in Modern Turkey is a close examination of the socioreligious practice of circumcision in twenty-five cities and their outlying towns and villages in Turkey. By analyzing the changing subjectivity of medical actors who seek to alleviate suffering in male circumcision, Başaran offers a psychoanalytically informed alternate approach to the standard sociological arguments surrounding medicalization and male circumcision.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aCircumcisionzTurkeyxHistoryy20th century. 0aCircumcisionzTurkeyxHistoryy21st century. 0aMedical personnelzTurkeyxSocial conditions. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aethnography, medical anthropology, gender in the Middle East, history of medicine, Male Circumcision, Medicine, Pain, Trauma, Psychoanalysis, Turkey, Middle East.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Cultural and Area Studies 2023 Englishz978311131909408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Cultural and Area Studies 2023z978311131812708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Texas Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z97831107978240 cprintz978147732702940uhttps://doi.org/10.7560/32702940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781477327036423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781477327036/original  a978-3-11-079782-4  University of Texas Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131812-7  EBOOK PACKAGE Cultural and Area Studies 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131909-4  EBOOK PACKAGE Cultural and